The paper discusses the need for a metadata management infrastructure for scientific data, which involves capturing and manipulating metadata during data production and analysis, storing metadata within datasets, and querying metadata through standardized interfaces. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), distributed and parallel computing (cs.DC), and software engineering (cs.SE).
